President Obama has declared a major disaster in the state of Arkansas due to severe storms, tornadoes, and flooding that occurred from May 30 to June 3, 2013. This declaration allows for federal aid to supplement state and local recovery efforts. Funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Kenneth K. Suiso has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, contact the FEMA news desk.